A SUMMIT aimed at optimising Nigeria's healthcare sector holds Thursday, April 26, 2018 at the Golden Gates Restaurant, Ikoyi, Lagos. In a statement, Emeka Achonu of Ashcole Communications, organisers of the Summit said the event brings together stakeholders in the healthcare industry to discuss sustainable ways to bring about better healthcare in Nigeria and Africa. Among the host of dignitaries expected at the event are the Minister of Health, Prof. Isaac Adewole and the Senior Special Assistant on the Sustainable Development Goals, SDGs, to the Presidency, Mrs. Adejoke Orelope-Adefulire and Consultant for World. Others include theLagos State Commissioner for Health, Dr. Olajide Idris; co-founders of the Anadach Group - Dr. Enoma Alade and Egbe Osifo Dawodu; Chief Executive Officer of Oceanic Health, Charles Onwuzuluigbo and CEO, Redcare HMO, Dr. Tunde Salako. The Chairman, Senate Committee on Health, Senator Lanre Tejouso, is expected to deliver the opening speech.